ons.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037198,0.063301,0.08125,0.093628,0.10095,0.10297,0.1063,0.10225,0.095269,0.084142,0.072409,0.060328],"unified_progress":[0.035776,0.065902,0.086533,0.099954,0.10535,0.11196,0.10469,0.097786,0.094448,0.080817,0.065407,0.051388]},{"section":15,"text":"The ERG is subnormal, which indicates that the retina isn't functioning properly.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031809,0.059574,0.081092,0.093712,0.10107,0.10322,0.10518,0.10186,0.097487,0.087632,0.076142,0.061237],"unified_progress":[0.035059,0.065204,0.08534,0.097352,0.10397,0.10938,0.1048,0.099473,0.095048,0.085366,0.068237,0.050774]},{"section":16,"text":"In retinitis pigmentosa, the ERG is typically abnormal because the photoreceptor cells are affected.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037632,0.056137,0.074676,0.088319,0.098616,0.10296,0.10723,0.10475,0.099694,0.089039,0.077152,0.063807],"unified_progress":[0.040166,0.067462,0.086944,0.098822,0.10501,0.10833,0.10389,0.097629,0.094006,0.081185,0.066106,0.050448]},{"section":17,"text":"Putting this all together: night blindness, tubular vision, ring scotoma, subnormal ERG, and the fundus findings like waxy disc and pigmentation spicules.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033822,0.064102,0.074931,0.080234,0.086353,0.088306,0.091246,0.091518,0.090719,0.090604,0.099067,0.1091],"unified_progress":[0.054171,0.08296,0.082914,0.08512,0.087078,0.088221,0.086896,0.088942,0.087619,0.081774,0.08514,0.089165]},{"section":18,"text":"These all point towards retinitis pigmentosa.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033579,0.059021,0.070282,0.078342,0.078504,0.079748,0.08318,0.086264,0.087626,0.097965,0.11109,0.1344],"unified_progress":[0.030622,0.051559,0.065385,0.075116,0.07799,0.083832,0.086928,0.091265,0.094852,0.097426,0.11209,0.13293]},{"section":19,"text":"It's a condition where the retina degenerates, affecting mainly the rods first, leading to night blindness and peripheral vision loss.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042757,0.056871,0.068557,0.077322,0.08463,0.089024,0.095364,0.098078,0.098782,0.097512,0.096178,0.094924],"unified_progress":[0.036211,0.055751,0.070116,0.079947,0.08729,0.094104,0.095073,0.098218,0.09979,0.097732,0.094972,0.090797]},{"section":20,"text":"The pigmentation in the midperipheral retina is also a hallmark of this disease.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031708,0.054298,0.071636,0.082756,0.090758,0.094774,0.099602,0.099908,0.099478,0.095897,0.091771,0.087414],"unified_progress":[0.031421,0.057803,0.07545,0.08674,0.093741,0.098152,0.098118,0.097618,0.099193,0.092299,0.087094,0.08237]},{"section":21,"text":"I don't think it's glaucoma because the IOP is normal, and the visual field loss here is more central with a ring scotoma, which doesn't fit the typical pattern of glaucoma.","dimension":0,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030864,0.053505,0.071086,0.081122,0.089364,0.093448,0.098322,0.10005,0.10101,0.099211,0.094623,0.087403],"unified_progress":[0.031994,0.057592,0.073162,0.083456,0.091291,0.097209,0.097767,0.099263,0.099402,0.097539,0.090375,0.080948]},{"section":22,"text":"Other possibilities like retinal detachment would present with more acute symptoms and different fundus findings.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041778,0.053868,0.067309,0.076049,0.085703,0.091337,0.097925,0.10083,0.10164,0.099583,0.095593,0.088381],"unified_progress":[0.041365,0.061629,0.073108,0.081904,0.088801,0.095717,0.0959,0.098583,0.09874,0.096225,0.089211,0.078816]},{"section":23,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis is retinitis pigmentosa.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023081,0.037064,0.047206,0.053993,0.061759,0.067848,0.074876,0.083781,0.091324,0.11781,0.1456,0.