is another clue.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047049,0.089382,0.093242,0.093922,0.092875,0.093465,0.09182,0.08935,0.088104,0.080807,0.073397,0.066588],"unified_progress":[0.049203,0.077752,0.087877,0.095438,0.099219,0.098608,0.096169,0.093819,0.091269,0.081615,0.07072,0.058312]},{"section":10,"text":"Ring scotoma is a central ring-shaped area of visual loss, which can occur in conditions like retinitis pigmentosa as the disease progresses, leading to a constriction of the visual field.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043339,0.078914,0.084856,0.092021,0.096724,0.098399,0.098772,0.093878,0.088598,0.083684,0.073268,0.067546],"unified_progress":[0.051289,0.065659,0.081636,0.089538,0.095123,0.10566,0.099071,0.096865,0.093221,0.085715,0.07406,0.06216]},{"section":11,"text":"Also, the ERG being subnormal (which I think means reduced) supports this because RP typically has a diminished ERG, especially the rod response first since night blindness is a symptom.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041214,0.081494,0.091398,0.095168,0.096239,0.095967,0.096589,0.092764,0.087215,0.083368,0.073999,0.064584],"unified_progress":[0.045493,0.074077,0.086858,0.093352,0.098564,0.099859,0.097944,0.094958,0.090631,0.08494,0.073911,0.059414]},{"section":12,"text":"Wait, but what about other differentials?","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029299,0.063437,0.0831,0.091652,0.097174,0.097047,0.09705,0.096317,0.095213,0.09174,0.08337,0.074601],"unified_progress":[0.037375,0.071335,0.083922,0.099801,0.098141,0.094812,0.097333,0.094066,0.090292,0.09542,0.077849,0.059654]},{"section":13,"text":"Like Refsum disease or Usher syndrome?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025344,0.059328,0.075586,0.087217,0.09683,0.10107,0.10356,0.10244,0.097781,0.097027,0.084916,0.068904],"unified_progress":[0.03442,0.067235,0.083292,0.092011,0.098514,0.1035,0.10263,0.10076,0.095289,0.090771,0.074603,0.05697]},{"section":14,"text":"But those usually have other systemic features.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.016096,0.045749,0.063985,0.076589,0.08732,0.09504,0.10669,0.11121,0.11178,0.10932,0.10426,0.071956],"unified_progress":[0.036015,0.05506,0.069976,0.078386,0.092126,0.094654,0.10033,0.1087,0.1072,0.11539,0.088822,0.053344]},{"section":15,"text":"The fundus findings here with the bone spicules and the ERG results are more specific.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023974,0.056238,0.070971,0.080071,0.08595,0.09144,0.096707,0.098495,0.10478,0.10219,0.099946,0.089239],"unified_progress":[0.030399,0.056807,0.072108,0.083515,0.091937,0.097543,0.10108,0.10134,0.10457,0.10026,0.090864,0.069575]},{"section":16,"text":"Also, RP is the most common inherited retinal dystrophy.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027431,0.057442,0.07058,0.080986,0.088403,0.092336,0.096215,0.095896,0.094707,0.098831,0.092996,0.10418],"unified_progress":[0.034362,0.052996,0.066054,0.076298,0.082867,0.093975,0.094441,0.098333,0.098608,0.099957,0.1004,0.10171]},{"section":17,"text":"The combination of night blindness, bone spicules, peripheral vision loss (tubular vision), ring scotoma on perimetry, and abnormal ERG all line up with retinitis pigmentosa.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03009,0.061407,0.070314,0.077841,0.085069,0.091212,0.095496,0.096539,0.099144,0.099559,0.098361,0.094969],"unified_progress":[0.035161,0.055547,0.067756,0.077122,0.085551,0.095635,0.096013,0.099671,0.10276,0.10159,0.097851,0.085342]},{"section":18,"text":"The optic disc pallor might be from secondary optic atrophy due to retinal degeneration rather than primary glaucoma, given the other findings.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028263,0.063084,0.075419,0.084503,0.089958,0.095458,0.098865,0.097139,0.10093,0.093992,0.088657,0.083733],"unified_progress":[0.032056,0.056576,0.072102,0.083171,0.09181,0.097073,0.098456,0.098621,0.10268,0.097102,0.0906,0.079757]},{"section":19,"text":"So putting it all together, the diagnosis is likely retinitis pigmentosa.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026403,0.048686,0.057291,0.064261,0.070966,0.076441,0.083444,0.088271,0.095679,0.10092,0.11317,0.17447],"unified_progress":[0.027558,0.034278,0.042595,0.05224,0.057929,0.069331,0.075547,0.089337,0.10083,0.10999,0.14738,0.19299]}]}}